author: ED GRUVER | Sports Writer
title: L-L Football Week 7: McCaskey, Warwick renew Section 1 rivalry
text:
Comments CHRIS KNIGHT 
McCaskey quarterback John Burnside (5), shown scrambling out of the pocket against Penn Manor on Friday October 9, 2015, rides herd on a talented Red Tornado offense.(Photo/Chris Knight) 
McCaskey (1-2 Section One, 2-4 overall) at Warwick (0-3 Section One, 1-5 overall): QB John Burnside keys a balanced Red Tornado attack riding high following a 28-0 win over Penn Manor. 
Burnside accounted for all four scores against the Comets, throwing touchdown strikes of 30 and 70 yards to QB=turned RB Jathan Gonzalez. Burnside also ran for two TDs as McCaskey produced 193 yards rushing and 175 passing. 
Kobe Gantz and Randolph Speller have combined for 36 receptions and 516 yards. 
Linebackers Skylar Davis, Michael Davis III and Greg Nunez and defensive back Ray Goodwin rank among the Red Tornado tackle leaders. Isaiah Speller has a team-high 2 interceptions. 
The Warriors look to pick up where they left off last Friday. Despite dropping a 34-29 decision at Conestoga Valley Warwick had a strong second half on offense. 
Tyler Trimarchi, Colin Gibble, Carter Forney and Owen Neff are among the playmakers in a Warwick attack that produced 424 yards last Friday. 
The Warwick-McCaskey series has been highly competitive over the past decade, each team winning five games. More Headlines
